]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The entire Digital Twin stack is hosted on the Raspberry Pi linked to the incubator. The low‑level driver, the bang‑bang controller, the RabbitMQ server, and the digital twin services that subscribe to message feeds all run locally on the Pi (edge deployment). The system stores aggregated data and time‑series records on the Pi’s onboard storage, with the possibility to publish it to external dashboards. The deployment is managed on‑premises, aligning with the documented “on‑premises and in the cloud” capability of RabbitMQ."
